<font color="#FF0000">SHOOTOUT AT THE OK CORRAL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jul 27 14:23:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To All,<br>
     Can't leave this site because of a computer bug for a few weeks, and WW III starts up.<br><br>
Doc,<br>
     So you've proved that you can dish out the garbage on the same level as the guys dumping on you.  Big Deal!  More heat and no light!<br><br>
Cook,<br>
     I have great respect for anyone that went through regular combat.  That said, am put off a bit by your chest beating.  Yeah and I can count on 2 hands the number of times I was under fire, ands not heavy at that.  It only takes one in the right spot.  Also, you should be ashamed of calling a traitor anyone who went through the legal process for conscientious objector and served as such.  That's part of what you fought for, or do you need to reread the bill of rights?  As for our cause, if it was so clear cut in the right; why wasn't war declared in accordance with our Constitution?  Suggest you read the recently published &quot;Dereliction of Duty&quot; by H.R. McMaster on how we got into Vietnam.<br>
     I'll be frank. I have a problem with people who come off as ideologues, whether of the right or left; especially when they show lack of respect for other persons as human beings.  Have met many Marines over the past 30 years, and am working with several right now at the Naval Depot in Philly, including a major that is one of the best examples of a real &quot;officer and a gentleman&quot; I've ever met.  There are a few things you could learn from him on how to treat people.<br>
     
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


